# Biography

<br><left>

My name is Luca Kozma [*'lutsa*] and I am a lecturer in the Division of Psychology and Social Work at the [University of the West of Scotland](https://research-portal.uws.ac.uk/en/persons/luca-kozma).

My research is focused on evolutionary human behaviour, more specifically on social perception and first impressions.

I am  a member of the [Psychological Science Accelerator](https://psysciacc.org/), [ManyFaces](https://manyfaces.team/), and the Local Nework Lead for the [UK Reproducibility Network](https://www.ukrn.org/)

In my spare time I like to do sports, read sci-fi and mystery novels, and listen to literary podcasts. I am an avid knitter, and I sing in a choir.</left>

<br>

